# **Red64 EngineValue Framework Executive Metrics Quick Reference Guide**

## **The Essential Business Metrics for Engineering Leadership**

---

## **Top 10 Metrics Every CEO/CFO Should Track**

### **1\. Engineering ROI**

**What:** Return on engineering investment  
 **Target:** 150%+ (Elite: 250%+)  
 **Why it matters:** Proves engineering creates value, not just consumes budget

### **2\. Time to Market**

**What:** Days from concept to customer delivery  
 **Target:** \<30 days (Elite: 15-23 days)  
 **Why it matters:** Speed to market \= competitive advantage

### **3\. Cost Per Feature**

**What:** Average cost to deliver a feature  
 **Target:** $30K-40K (Industry avg: $52.8K)  
 **Why it matters:** Unit economics of engineering output

### **4\. On-Time Delivery Rate**

**What:** % of commitments delivered on schedule  
 **Target:** 85%+ (Elite: 90%+)  
 **Why it matters:** Predictability enables better business planning

### **5\. Engineering Efficiency Index**

**What:** Composite score of speed, quality, and cost  
 **Target:** 80+ (Elite: 85+)  
 **Why it matters:** Holistic view of engineering performance

### **6\. Change Failure Rate**

**What:** % of deployments causing production issues  
 **Target:** \<5% (Elite: 0-5%)  
 **Why it matters:** Quality directly impacts customer satisfaction and costs

### **7\. Technical Debt Ratio**

**What:** % of codebase requiring refactoring  
 **Target:** \<15% (Elite: \<10%)  
 **Why it matters:** Predicts future velocity and maintenance costs

### **8\. Strategic Alignment Score**

**What:** % of engineering effort on strategic goals  
 **Target:** 70%+  
 **Why it matters:** Ensures engineering drives business strategy

### **9\. Cost Per Developer (Output)**

**What:** Business value created per engineer  
 **Target:** $400K-500K/year (Industry avg: $392K)  
 **Why it matters:** Measures true productivity and hiring ROI

### **10\. AI Adoption ROI**

**What:** Return on AI coding tools investment  
 **Target:** 300%+ (Elite teams: 1,000%+)  
 **Why it matters:** Validates modern tooling investments

## **Metric Categories at a Glance**

### **Financial Metrics (CFO Focus)**

| Metric | Formula | Target |
| ----- | ----- | ----- |
| Engineering ROI | (Value \- Cost) / Cost × 100 | 150-250% |
| Cost per Feature | Total Costs / Features Delivered | $30-40K |
| Cost per Developer | Value Generated / \# Engineers | $400-500K/yr |
| Dev Cost per Story Point | Total Costs / Story Points | Decreasing trend |
| Engineering Cost % of Revenue | Eng Costs / Revenue × 100 | 15-30% (depends on stage) |

### **Speed Metrics (CEO Focus)**

| Metric | Definition | Target |
| ----- | ----- | ----- |
| Time to Market | Concept to customer availability | \<30 days |
| Lead Time for Changes | Commit to production | \<1 day (Elite) |
| Deployment Frequency | Releases per day/week | Daily+ (Elite) |
| Feature Velocity | Features per quarter | 8-12+ |
| Cycle Time | Start to delivery | \<10 days |

### **Efficiency Metrics (Ops Focus)**

| Metric | What It Measures | Target |
| ----- | ----- | ----- |
| Engineering Efficiency Index | Composite performance score | 80+ |
| Throughput | Value items completed | Stable/improving |
| Flow Efficiency | Active time / total time | \>25% |
| Sprint Predictability | Commitments met | 85%+ |
| Capacity Utilization | Planned work % | 75-85% |

### **Quality Metrics (Risk Focus)**

| Metric | Impact | Target |
| ----- | ----- | ----- |
| Change Failure Rate | Deployment quality | \<5% |
| MTTR | Recovery speed | \<1 hour (Elite) |
| Technical Debt Ratio | Code health | \<15% |
| Customer Defects | Quality perception | \<15/month |
| Security Response Time | Risk mitigation | \<24hrs (Critical) |

MTTR: Mean time to repair (or Recovery)

## **Example Quick ROI Calculations** 

### **AI Coding Tools ROI**

Investment: 50 engineers × $20/month × 12 \= $12,000/year  
Productivity gain: 25% × $7.5M salary \= $1,875M  
ROI: 15,525% 

### **Engineering Efficiency Improvement ROI**

Current: $500K/month, 12 features \= $41.7K/feature  
After 20% improvement: $500K/month, 15 features \= $33.3K/feature  
Savings: $8.4K per feature × 180 features/year \= $1.5M/year

### **Technical Debt Reduction ROI**

Current debt: 23% of capacity lost  
Target: 12% of capacity lost  
Team: 50 engineers @ $150K avg \= $7.5M/year  
Capacity recovered: 11% × $7.5M \= $825K/year

## **Key Benchmarks by Industry**

### **SaaS/Cloud Companies**

* Engineering Cost % of Revenue: 20-30%  
* Time to Market: 15-30 days  
* Deployment Frequency: Multiple per day  
* Engineering ROI: 200-300%

### **Enterprise Software**

* Engineering Cost % of Revenue: 15-25%  
* Time to Market: 30-60 days  
* Deployment Frequency: Weekly to monthly  
* Engineering ROI: 150-200%

### **Startup/High Growth**

* Engineering Cost % of Revenue: 30-50%  
* Time to Market: 7-20 days  
* Deployment Frequency: Multiple per day  
* Engineering ROI: Variable (invest for growth)

## **DORA Metrics Performance Levels**

### **Elite Performers**

* Deploy Frequency: On-demand (100+ per day)  
* Lead Time: \< 1 hour  
* MTTR: \< 1 hour  
* Change Failure Rate: 0-5%

### **High Performers**

* Deploy Frequency: Daily to weekly  
* Lead Time: 1 day to 1 week  
* MTTR: \< 1 day  
* Change Failure Rate: 5-15%

### **Medium Performers**

* Deploy Frequency: Weekly to monthly  
* Lead Time: 1 week to 1 month  
* MTTR: 1 day to 1 week  
* Change Failure Rate: 16-30%

### **Low Performers**

* Deploy Frequency: Monthly to every 6 months  
* Lead Time: 1 month to 6 months  
* MTTR: \> 1 week  
* Change Failure Rate: \> 30%

## **Framing Metrics for Different Audiences**

### **For the Board**

"Our engineering efficiency index of 82 places us in the top quartile. This translates to 40% faster time to market than industry average, enabling us to capture market opportunities before competitors."

### **For the CEO**

"Engineering ROI of 256% means every dollar invested in engineering returns $2.56 in business value. This quarter, we've identified $592K in optimization opportunities without adding headcount."

### **For the CFO**

"Our cost per feature of $36.5K is 31% below industry average of $52.8K. This efficiency enables us to deliver 40% more features with the same budget, or save $2.9M annually at current delivery rates."

### **For Investors**

"Technical debt ratio of 12% versus industry average of 24% means we spend 50% less time on maintenance, allowing more investment in innovation. Our deployment frequency of 12x daily enables rapid response to market needs."

## **Red Flags to Watch For**

### **Financial Red Flags**

* Engineering ROI \< 100%  
* Cost per feature increasing \>10% quarter-over-quarter  
* Engineering cost \> 35% of revenue (mature companies)  
* Technical debt costs increasing

### **Operational Red Flags**

* On-time delivery \< 65%  
* Time to market increasing  
* Deployment frequency decreasing  
* Change failure rate \> 20%

### **Quality Red Flags**

* MTTR \> 4 hours  
* Technical debt ratio \> 25%  
* Customer defects increasing  
* Security vulnerabilities unpatched \>30 days

### **Strategic Red Flags**

* Strategic alignment \< 60%  
* Innovation rate \< 30%  
* Feature adoption \< 50%  
* High-value projects delayed repeatedly
